   {:e #blake3 "aed7e3f9b3eab7b117f144d56776e57404c4abae0eaddcdb628c69a435f5b5b5" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-65dd941c42b2331b; GENESIS-2: THE CONCEPT AS MISSING PRIMITIVE. Knowledge emerges through CONCEPT CRYSTALLIZATION — not through keyword matching, not through structured flags, not through extractors. A concept is a first-class entity in the store that represents a cluster of meaning, evolves over time, and connects observations through shared conceptual membership. Concepts are: (1) EMERGENT — they arise when the system detects multiple observations cluster in embedding space. Not predefined by taxonomy. (2) MUTABLE — via retract-then-assert. As observations accumulate, description and embedding update. Concepts split when internal variance exceeds threshold, merge when centroids converge. (3) BRIDGES ACROSS AGENTS — new agents inherit concepts, not raw observations. The seed shows 'Known concepts: event-sourcing (7 obs), error-suppression (6 obs)' — a conceptual vocabulary, not a data dump. (4) SOLVE SYNONYMY — two agents use different tags for same pattern; concept embeddings detect semantic proximity and propose merge. (5) EVOLVE WITH THE GRAPH — each new observation updates concept membership and centroid. The concept graph IS the knowledge structure. Formal definition: a concept is an entity with (:concept/name String One), (:concept/description String One), (:concept/embedding Bytes One — centroid of member embeddings), (:concept/member-count Long One), (:concept/created-at Long One). Observations link via (:exploration/concept Ref Many). This implements OBSERVER-6 (Ontology Discovery) from the bedrock vision: 'observation clustering → proposed categories.'; GENESIS-1: DOGFOOD-2 Session 2 ROOT CAUSE CHAIN. Surface: connections scored 3.0/10 (Jaccard keyword similarity). One level down: the connection engine treats observations as bags of words — it has no model of what the observations are ABOUT. Two levels down: braid has NO MODEL OF THE PROJECT AT ALL — it stores text strings, not structural knowledge. Three levels down: the LLM agent already HAD the structural knowledge (it read the code, understood imports, traced dependencies) but when it communicated via braid observe, all structure was discarded by keyword tokenization. Deepest: the interface between LLM (rich associative structure) and braid (persistent store) is a LOSSY FUNNEL. The LLM's activation space encodes ~100K bits of semantic information per observation. The keyword bag retains ~100 bits. This is an information-theoretic bottleneck, not a connection-algorithm bug. The five solutions proposed earlier (multi-signal connections, coverage map, trajectory response, bootstrap surfacing, clustering) are all HEURISTICS TO COMPENSATE FOR NOT PRESERVING THE LLM'S SEMANTIC STRUCTURE. The real fix: preserve the LLM's associative structure at observation intake time.; Session entity: :session/s-1774407115; GENESIS-7: BOOTSTRAP HYPOTHESIS SURFACING IN STATUS — THE FIRST STEERING VECTOR. On fresh projects, braid status should surface bootstrap hypotheses as the FIRST interaction. This is the Markov blanket's first emission — the moment that primes the LLM's exploration trajectory. Current: 'store: .braid (335 datoms). M(t): 0.35.' Proposed: 'project: Go module (62,490 LOC, 38 packages). Detected: event-driven architecture (events/, materialize/). Detected: 5-tier engine (consistency/). Detected: CLI framework (~50 commands). Innate schemas: components (38 detected, 0 explored), dependencies (0 mapped), invariants (0 verified), patterns (0 identified), anomalies (0 found). Start: braid observe what you notice.' The innate schemas aren't instructions — they're ACTIVATION PATTERNS. They prime the LLM toward structured investigation by presenting incomplete knowledge that the LLM wants to complete. Orientation regressed 4.3→3.3 because fresh init showed nothing. This fix: ~50 LOC in status.rs, zero new architecture. Immediate impact on DOGFOOD orientation score.; GENESIS-8: EXPLORATION COVERAGE MAP FROM CONCEPT MEMBERSHIP. Once packages are entities (from bootstrap) and observations auto-link to packages (entity resolution), coverage = packages-with-observations / total-packages. But with concepts, coverage becomes richer: coverage = packages-covered-by-at-least-one-concept / total-packages. The FRONTIER is computable: packages that are imported by observed packages but not yet observed. This enables the discovery dimension: 'you explored materialize but not its dependency cascade — cascade imports materialize, causal, and projector.' Status shows: 'coverage: 12/38 packages (32%). Concepts span 8 distinct subsystems. Frontier: cascade, projector, causal (all imported by explored packages).' This directly solves Discovery (2.3→6+ target). The coverage map is not a separate data structure — it is a DATALOG QUERY over existing datoms: [:find (count ?pkg) :where [?obs :exploration/mentions-entity ?pkg] [?pkg :db/ident ?ident] [(str/starts-with? ?ident ':pkg/')]].; GENESIS-6: ENTITY AUTO-LINKING — BRAID UNDERSTANDS WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT. When braid observe receives text, it should scan for known entity names (package names from bootstrap, concept names, spec IDs from prior observations) and auto-create Ref datoms linking the observation to those entities. Example: 'the materialize engine...' matches :pkg/internal-materialize from bootstrap → auto-link :observation/X :exploration/mentions-entity :pkg/internal-materialize. This is the minimum viable 'braid understands structure' — not through NLP or embeddings (those provide semantic similarity), but through simple string matching against its own entity inventory. It works because bootstrap already created the entity inventory. No new flags, no --about syntax. The agent writes natural language. Braid does entity resolution. Combined with embeddings: entity auto-linking provides STRUCTURAL connections (same package mentioned), while embeddings provide SEMANTIC connections (conceptually similar even without shared entities). Together they close 100% of the DOGFOOD-2 missed connections: materialize↔events (entity co-reference + semantic similarity), INV-019↔INV-021 (spec-ref co-location + semantic similarity), error-suppression×6 (concept clustering via embedding similarity).; GENESIS-5: THE CLI AS MARKOV BLANKET — STATUS/OBSERVE AS LATENT SPACE STEERING. The deepest architectural insight: every braid CLI response is a STEERING VECTOR injected into the LLM's context window, shaping attention, exploration direction, and conceptual vocabulary. The CLI is a Markov blanket — the boundary across which the store's state (persistent model) and the LLM's state (transient model) exchange information. braid status is not a dashboard — it is a PROMPT. braid observe response is not an acknowledgment — it is a NAVIGATION AID. The quality of these responses determines the agent's entire exploration trajectory. The SINGLE SMARTEST ADDITION: after braid observe, return a concept-contextualized response that navigates the LLM's latent space toward the highest-value next observation. Three lines: (1) concept membership — 'this observation joined concept:event-processing (3 members)' — activates the LLM's schema for that area, (2) structural gap — 'this concept spans events/, materialize/ but not cascade/ (imports materialize, unexplored)' — the acquisition function as natural language, (3) the steering question — 'what happens when the fold encounters a malformed event?' — derived from the intersection of the current concept and the nearest unconnected concept. The question is COMPUTABLE from the concept graph: take current concept, find nearest concept sharing no entities, ask about the boundary between them. Specific, falsifiable, structurally derived — not a template.; Session entity: :task/t-1b8420a3; Session entity: :task/t-f9dfbcdc; Session entity: :task/t-73d4a210; GENESIS-4: EMBEDDING INFRASTRUCTURE via frankensearch/model2vec. Semantic embeddings preserve the LLM's associative structure — two observations about the same subsystem have nearby embeddings even with zero keyword overlap. The enabling technology: model2vec/potion-128M (256-dim, safetensors, no API calls, ~0.5ms per embedding, deterministic output). This is a static embedder — vocabulary lookup + mean-pool, not a neural network forward pass. From safetensors file, fully offline, C8-compatible. frankensearch already packages this: two-tier embedding (fast: potion-128M 256-dim, quality: MiniLM-L6-v2 384-dim), FSVI vector storage, BM25+vector hybrid search via Reciprocal Rank Fusion. For braid: at observe time, compute 256-dim embedding of observation text, store as :exploration/embedding Bytes datom. Connection scoring becomes cosine similarity on embeddings — O(concepts) per observation. For concept centroids: running mean of member embeddings. For concept matching: cosine(observation_embedding, concept_centroid) > JOIN_THRESHOLD. This replaces Jaccard as the PRIMARY connection signal. Jaccard remains as fallback when embeddings unavailable. Dependency: frankensearch crate or model2vec directly. ~5MB binary size increase (safetensors model file). No API calls. No network. Deterministic.; Session entity: :recon/trace-5804bf1c1f0c1187; Session entity: :recon/trace-25cbb4eb3396a2be; Session entity: :recon/trace-698d5f0cb07c8cff; CE-GATE-A RESULT: STOP. DOGFOOD-2 Session 2 scored 3.3/10 (BELOW Session 1's 4.0/10). Phase A did NOT improve the agent experience. REGRESSION ROOT CAUSES: (1) Connection quality 3.0/10 — Jaccard keyword similarity missed semantically obvious relationships. Agent A: materialize↔events not connected despite direct import relationship. Agent C: consistency package cluster (INV-019, INV-021) not detected despite same package. Agent B: error suppression pattern across 6 files not recognized as recurring theme. (2) Responsiveness 2.7/10 — micro-hypothesis template 'Does X interact with Y?' was mechanical and formulaic. 'No connections yet. What else relates to this?' appeared 70% of the time. No adaptation to exploration trajectory. (3) Orientation 3.3/10 — REGRESSED because fresh init lost Session 1 knowledge. Bootstrap hypotheses existed but were not surfaced in status or seed. Agents had no map of the Go CLI to start from. (4) Persistence 5.0/10 — REGRESSED from 6.3 because fresh init meant no accumulated knowledge. Within-session persistence worked but observations did not compound. (5) Discovery 2.3/10 — FLAT. Braid recorded findings but did not help find them. One genuine discovery assist (Agent A cycle 5: absorb↔annotate via keyword overlap). BRIGHT SPOTS: (a) cotx[task] auto-creation was valued by agents B and C. (b) Boundary measurement appeared (0.67-0.88 scores). (c) M(t) responded to activity (0.35→0.59). (d) Agents valued the discipline of articulated observations. PHASE A HYPOTHESIS FALSIFIED: Keyword Jaccard + hub-preferential attachment is insufficient for meaningful connections. Semantic similarity (embeddings or structural co-location) required.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ada704c87714efef; Session entity: :recon/trace-6843239801cb0c9f; GENESIS-3: PIAGETIAN DEVELOPMENTAL EPISTEMOLOGY FOR KNOWLEDGE STORES. Children don't learn by accumulating facts — they construct SCHEMAS that organize experience (Piaget's genetic epistemology). Schemas evolve through: ASSIMILATION (new experience fits existing schema), DISEQUILIBRIUM (experience doesn't fit), ACCOMMODATION (schema restructures). Stages are qualitatively different structures, not more data in the same structure: sensorimotor → preoperational → concrete operational → formal operational. Applied to braid: a fresh store needs INNATE SCHEMAS — universal cognitive structures that provide initial scaffolding for concept formation. Five innate schemas for code exploration: COMPONENTS (parts and boundaries), DEPENDENCIES (how parts relate), INVARIANTS (what should hold true), PATTERNS (recurring regularities), ANOMALIES (deviations from patterns). These are not Go-specific or braid-specific — they are universal for understanding structured artifacts. They are the Piagetian 'sensorimotor reflexes' that make assimilation possible before domain knowledge exists. At braid init, seed these as initial concept entities with pre-computed embeddings. The developmental trajectory: sensorimotor (innate schemas + raw observations) → concrete operational (domain-specific concepts like 'event-sourcing') → formal operational (cross-cutting abstractions like 'append-only guarantee'). MEMETIC TRANSMISSION: concepts that emerge on one project transfer to another via CRDT merge. Concepts that prove useful across projects get selected. This is cultural evolution — memes competing and being selected for fitness across environments. Braid's self-knowledge (42 sessions) becomes the genome for offspring sessions.; Session entity: :task/t-e5dc085e; Session entity: :recon/trace-1cbf8c53a5ed0781; Session entity: :recon/trace-15aeec73f020d8ee; Session entity: :task/t-5a20a676; Session entity: :task/t-23ec839a; Session entity: :recon/trace-ccec040e6ded7690\nSession entity: :task/t-1eb0b302; Session entity: :task/t-455bbfa1" :op :assert}
